elements.description:
`api-documentation`

A main documentation view for AMF model.

This element works with [AMF](https://github.com/mulesoft/amf) data model.

It works well with `api-navigation` component. When `handle-navigation-events`
is set it listens for selection events dispatched by the navigation.

To manually steare the behavior of the component you have to set both:
- selected
- selectedType

Selected is an `@id` of the AMF data model in json/ld representation.
Selected type tells the component where to look for the data and which
view to render.

The component handles data computation on selection change.

## Updating API's base URI

By default the component render the documentation as it is defined
in the AMF model. Sometimes, however, you may need to replace the base URI
of the API with something else. It is useful when the API does not
have base URI property defined (therefore this component render relative
paths instead of URIs) or when you want to manage different environments.

To update base URI value either update `baseUri` property or use
`iron-meta` with key `ApiBaseUri`. First method is easier but the second
gives much more flexibility since it use a
[monostate pattern](http://wiki.c2.com/?MonostatePattern)
to manage base URI property.

When the component constructs the funal URI for the endpoint it does the following:
- if `baseUri` is set it uses this value as a base uri for the endpoint
- else if `iron-meta` with key `ApiBaseUri` exists and contains a value
it uses it uses this value as a base uri for the endpoint
- else if `amfModel` is set then it computes base uri value from main
model document
Then it concatenates computed base URI with `endpoint`'s path property.

### Example

```html
<iron-meta key="ApiBaseUri" value="https://domain.com"></iron-meta>
```

To update value of the `iron-meta`:
```javascript
new Polymer.IronMeta({key: 'ApiBaseUri'}).value = 'https://other.domain';
```

Note: The element will not be notified about the change when `iron-meta` value change.
The change will be reflected when `amfModel` or `endpoint` property chnage.

## Styling

`<api-documentation>` provides the following custom properties and mixins for styling:

Custom property | Description | Default
----------------|-------------|----------
`--api-documentation` | Mixin applied to this elment | `{}`

properties.name: selected
properties.description:
A model's `@id` of selected documentation part.
Special case is for `summary` view. It's not part of an API
but most applications has some kind of summary view for the
API.

properties.name: selectedType
properties.description:
Type of the selected item.
One of `documentation`, `type`, `security`, `endpoint`, `method`
or `summary`.

properties.name: handleNavigationEvents
properties.description:
By default application hosting the element must set `selected` and
`selectedType` properties. When using `api-navigation` element
by setting this property the element listens for navigation events
and updates the state

properties.name: isEndpoint
properties.description: True if currently selection is endpoint

properties.name: isMethod
properties.description: True if currently selection is method

properties.name: isDoc
properties.description: True if currently selection is documentation

properties.name: isType
properties.description: True if currently selection is type

properties.name: isSecurity
properties.description: True if currently selection is security

properties.name: isSummary
properties.description: True if currently selection is summary

properties.name: docsModel
properties.description:
Computed value of the final model extracted from `amfModel`, `selected`,
and `selectedType` properties.

properties.name: endpoint
properties.description: Computed value of currently rendered endpoint.

properties.name: baseUri
properties.description: A property to set to override AMF's model base URI information.

properties.name: noTryIt
properties.description:
Passing value of `noTryIt` to the method documentation.
Hiddes "Try it" button.

properties.name: narrow
properties.description: If set it will renders the view in the narrow layout.

properties.name: inlineMethods
properties.description:
If set then it renders methods documentation inline with
the endpoint documentation.
When it's not set (or value is `false`, default) then it renders
just a list of methods with links.

properties.name: scrollTarget
properties.description:
Scroll target used to observe `scroll` event.
When set the element will observe scroll and inform other components
about changes in navigation while scrolling through methods list.
The navigation event contains `passive: true` property that
determines that it's not user triggered navigation but rather
context enforced.

properties.name: redirectUri
properties.description:
OAuth2 redirect URI.
This value **must** be set in order for OAuth 1/2 to work properly.
This is only required in inline mode (`inlineMethods`).

methods.name: _registerNavigationEvents
methods.description:
Registers `api-navigation-selection-changed` event listener handler
on window object.

methods.name: _unregisterNavigationEvents
methods.description:
Removes event listener from window object for
`api-navigation-selection-changed` event.

methods.name: _handleNavChanged
methods.description: Registers / unregisters event listeners depending on `state`

methods.name: _navigationHandler
methods.description: Handler for `api-navigation-selection-changed` event.

methods.name: _apiModelChanged
methods.description:
A function that is called each time `amfModel`, `selected`, or `selectedType`
changed. It calls `__processModel()` function in a debouncer (Polymer's
`afterNextRender` from RenderStatus class) to ensure all properties are set.

Note, this function won't be called when any change inside `amfModel` ocurred
as this reacts on complete variable change.

methods.name: __processModel
methods.description:
Processes AMF model depending on it's type.
The documentation panel supports full API model, (some) RAML fragments,
and "partial" model returned from the query serice based on graph queries.

Note, this function throws an error if unsuported data is passed.

params.name: selectedType
params.description:
Selected view type. One of `endpoint`, `method`,
`documentation`, `type`, `security`, or `summary`.

params.name: inlineMethods
params.description:
Whether the view should render the request panel
alongside the documentation.

methods.name: __resetComponentSelection
methods.description:
Sets current component selection to the one specified in `selectedType`.
It does not change anything if current selection equals desired selection.

methods.name: __processApiSpecSelection
methods.description:
Processes selection for the web API data model. It ignores the input if
`selected` or `selectedType` is not set.

params.name: model
params.description: WebApi AMF model. Do not use an array here.

params.name: selectedType
params.description:
Currently selected view type. One of `endpoint`, `method`,
`documentation`, `type`, `security`, or `summary`.

methods.name: _computeSecurityApiModel
methods.description:
Computes security scheme definition model from web API and current selection.
It looks for the definition in both `declares` and `references` properties.
Returned value is already resolved AMF model (references are resolved).

params.name: model
params.description: WebApi AMF model. Do not use an array here.

return.desc: Model definition for the securit scheme.

methods.name: _computeTypeApiModel
methods.description:
Computes type definition model from web API and current selection.
It looks for the definition in both `declares` and `references` properties.
Returned value is already resolved AMF model (references are resolved).

params.name: model
params.description: WebApi AMF model. Do not use an array here.

methods.name: _computeDocsApiModel
methods.description: Computes documentation definition model from web API and current selection.

params.name: model
params.description: WebApi AMF model. Do not use an array here.

return.desc: Model definition for a documentation fragment.

methods.name: _computeEndpointApiModel
methods.description: Computes Endpoint definition model from web API and current selection.

params.name: model
params.description: WebApi AMF model. Do not use an array here.

return.desc: Model definition for an endpoint fragment.

methods.name: _computeMethodApiModel
methods.description: Computes Method definition model from web API and current selection.

params.name: model
params.description: WebApi AMF model. Do not use an array here.

return.desc: Model definition for an endpoint fragment.

methods.name: __processLibrarySelection
methods.description:
Processes selection for a library data model. It ignores the input if
`selected` or `selectedType` is not set.

params.name: model
params.description: Library AMF model. Do not use an array here.

params.name: selectedType
params.description:
Currently selected view type. One of `type` and `security`.
Other values, even though it may exists in the library, is not currently supported.

methods.name: _computeSecurityLibraryModel
methods.description: Computes Security scheme from a Library model.

methods.name: _computeTypeLibraryModel
methods.description: Computes Type definition from a Library model.

methods.name: _processSecurityFragment
methods.description:
Extracts security model from security scheme fragment and sets current selection
and the model.

methods.name: _processDocumentationFragment
methods.description:
Extracts documentation model from documentation fragment and sets current selection
and the model.

methods.name: _processTypeFragment
methods.description:
Extracts Type model from Type fragment and sets current selection
and the model.

methods.name: __processFragment
methods.description: Processes fragment model and sets current selection and the model.

methods.name: _processEndpointParial
methods.description:
Processes endpoint data from partial model definitnion.
It sets models that are used by the docs.

If `selected` or `selectedType` is not set then it automatically selects
an endpoint.

methods.name: _computeEndpointLink
methods.description:
Creates a link model that is accepted by the endpoint documentation
view.

params.name: item
params.description: An AMF shape to use to get the data from.

return.desc:
Object with `label` and `id` or `undefined`
if no item.

methods.name: _computeEndpointPrevious
methods.description:
Computes link model for previous endpoint, if any exists relative to
current selection.

return.desc:
Object with `label` and `id` or `undefined`
if no previous item.

methods.name: _computeEndpointNext
methods.description:
Computes link model for next endpoint, if any exists relative to
current selection.

return.desc:
Object with `label` and `id` or `undefined`
if no next item.

methods.name: _computeMethodLink
methods.description:
Creates a link model that is accepted by the method documentation
view.

params.name: item
params.description: An AMF shape to use to get the data from.

return.desc:
Object with `label` and `id` or `undefined`
if no item.

methods.name: _computeMethodPrevious
methods.description:
Computes link for the previous method.
This is used by the method documentation panel to render previous
nethod link.

return.desc:
Object with `label` and `id` or `undefined`
if no previous item.

methods.name: _computeMethodNext
methods.description:
Computes link for the next method.
This is used by the method documentation panel to render next
nethod link.

return.desc:
Object with `label` and `id` or `undefined`
if no next item.

methods.name: _computeMethodPartialEndpoint
methods.description: Computes method definition from an endpoint partial model.

methods.name: _renderInlineEndpoint
methods.description:
Tests if endpoint component should be rendered for both method and
endpoint documentation in inline mode.

methods.name: _renderEndpoint
methods.description: Computes if single endpoint doc should be rendered

methods.name: _renderMethod
methods.description: Computes if single method doc should be rendered

methods.name: _isLibrary
methods.description: Tests if `model` is of a RAML library model.

methods.name: _computeReferenceSecurity
methods.description: Computes a security model from a reference (library for example).

params.name: reference
params.description: AMF model for a reference to extract the data from

return.desc: Type definition or undefined if not found.

methods.name: _computeDeclById
methods.description: Computes model of a shape defined ni `declares` list

methods.name: _computeApiMediaTypes
methods.description:
Computes API's media types when requesting type documentation view.
This is passed to the type documentation to render examples in the type
according to API's defined media type.

return.desc: List of supported media types or undefined.
